headline: DTE Energy (DTE) Margin Dip Raises Fresh Questions on Profitability Narrative
summary: DTE Energy (DTE) posted a net profit margin of 10.1%, down from 11.2% a year ago, while reporting 4% earnings growth, noticeably slower than its five-year average rate of 11.7%. Revenue is forecast to grow at 3.7% per year, lagging the broader US market’s expected 10.3% pace, and analysts see earnings climbing by 8.01% per year. Investors will see a mixed picture: the company’s valuation sits above some industry measures but remains less expensive than peer averages, and persistent questions...
